      <hedline>
        <hl1>For a West Side Stadium</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Tim Zagat letter commends September 25 editorial backing construction of football stadium on Manhattan's West Side</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Development for New York City'' (editorial, Sept. 25):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Development for New York City'' (editorial, Sept. 25):</p>
        <p>As chairman of NYC &amp; Company-the Convention and Visitors Bureau, I commend you for focusing on the need to expand the Jacob K. Javits Convention Center and the addition of a stadium as part of an overall West Side development plan. As you note, the stadium could be used to supplement convention space.</p>
        <p>Last year, New York City broke all tourism records by welcoming some 37 million visitors. That's a total economic impact of $23 billion. But only 9 percent of those visitors were convention delegates.</p>
        <p>In reality, our convention business is very small compared with that of other convention cities like Las Vegas, Orlando and Chicago, whose convention centers will soon be more than double ours. Frankly, we've been left behind, and every day we're losing major revenues. It's time to bring this economic development program to fruition.</p>
        <p>TIM ZAGAT  New York, Sept. 26, 2000</p>
      </block>
